  "commentary": "With SPX at 6575.91 trading below the GEX flip at 6595, dealers are positioned to buy dips as we're in the positive gamma regime but below the flip point. The massive gamma wall at 6600 (+23B) combined with the PIN regime creates strong resistance above, while the negative gamma pocket at 6550 (-11B) provides support where dealers will aggressively buy any selloff. The recent GEX surge event suggests options flow is amplifying the current setup, with dealers likely to fade any move toward 6595-6600 resistance zone.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get pulled back toward 6590-6595 with limited upside past 6600.",
